A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 3 of Chapter 2 of Title 46 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to investigations and hearings of the Public Service Commission, so as to revise
3 provisions concerning discovery rights in proceedings before the Public Service
4 Commission; to provide for related maters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
6 SECTION 1.
7 Article 3 of Chapter 2 of Title 46 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
8 investigations and hearings of the Public Service Commission, is amended by revising Code
9 Section 46-2-57, relating to obtaining of discovery by employees and agents of commission,
10 petitions by commission for necessary orders, injunctions, and subpoenas, extension of
11 suspension period by Superior Court of Fulton County, and time of hearing of applications
12 and petitions from commission, as follows:
13 "46-2-57.
14 (a) In any case pending before it, the commission, in addition to its now existing authority
15 to do so, is authorized to issue an order permitting its employees and agents to take
16 depositions and otherwise obtain discovery of any matter, not privileged, which is relevant
